body:
I really like this. It also allows custom password providers to grab passwords in complex ways.

@gianm  / @nishantmonu51 how would you feel about just making this an environment variable provider? it uses passwordprovider so the name of EnvironmentVariablePasswordProvider is accurate, but can we change the field to just "variable" instead of "passwordVariable"?

I can see a scenario where you have an internal PasswordProvider that can take sub-PasswordProviders as parameters...  for example:

``` json
{
  "type":"companyPassFetcher",
  "key": "s0m3_k34",
  "secret":{
    "type":"environment",
    "variable":"SOME_DRUID_SECRET"
  }
}
```

where `key` and `secret` are both just PasswordProviders

@skoppar seems like you have specified the properties at wrong place in json spec file, 
the properties needs to be defined outside the spec block in json as done here - 
https://github.com/druid-io/tranquility/blob/master/distribution/src/universal/conf/kafka.json.example
